One of the awaiting trial prisoners who escaped from police custody while being transported from Lephalale to Polokwane in Limpopo has been re-arrested. Petrus Moyo was re-arrested in Ga-Mushi village. Moyo and Witness Simango allegedly cut through the roof of a moving police vehicle, jumped off, and then vanished into the nearby bushes. The local police were summoned and a manhunt ensued where Moyo was then re-arrested.